author: Greg Bluestein
title: Ga. leaders poised to enter DeKalb fray
text:
DeKalb Interim CEO Lee May's troubles may just be beginning.
Georgia's governor and attorney general signaled Monday they could take action against him, once the Georgia Bureau of Investigation completes a review of a corruption probe issued last week.
May also confronts calls for him to resign from several DeKalb groups. The CEO has scheduled several town hall meetings to respond to questions from DeKalb residents beginning Thursday.
